Basic definition of kubernetes yaml

apiVersion:      #Version defenition (v1)
kind:            #type of resource available in kubernetes (pod, replicaset, deployement,services,cronjobs etc)
metadata:        # used to define the below
  name:
  labels:
  namespace:
spec:            #Specification or real definition for the k8's objects



pod definition:

apiVersion: v1 #string
kind: pod #string
metadata: #list
  name: first pod
  labels: #Dictionary
    app: firstapp #key value pair
spec:
  containers:
    -name: firstapp
     image: python3.9
     ports:
      -conatainerport: 80


After deploying this run the below command

kubectl apply -f app.yaml


Create a load balancer service yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: service
metadata: 
  name: firstapp-loadbalancer
spec:
  type:LoadBalancer, cluster ip, nodeport (anyone thing)
  selector: 
    app: firstapp  # this should be the exactname labels that is defined in the pod section
  port:80 #service port
  targetport: 80 #container port

After deploying this run the below command

kubectl apply -f service.yaml


#hola your first application is created.

    

